Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.83,0:00:05.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙就是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cosmos is all there is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.58,0:00:06.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}过去是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or ever was,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.28,0:00:08.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以后还是这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or ever will be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:11.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}跟我来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.53,0:00:14.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}30多年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A generation ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.54,0:00:16.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天文学家卡尔·萨根站在这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the astronomer Carl Sagan stood here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.54,0:00:20.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}1980年 卡尔·萨根在PBS拍摄了纪录片《卡尔·萨根的宇宙》\n其纪录片在超过60个国家播出 影响着全世界超过五亿人口
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.94,0:00:18.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带领全世界数亿人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and launched hundreds of millions of us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.94,0:00:20.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}进行了一场历险\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on a great adventure...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.94,0:00:24.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用科学去探索宇宙的奥秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the exploration of the universe revealed by science.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.78,0:00:27.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是时候再次探险了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's time to get going again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.78,0:00:30.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这场即将开始的旅行会向我们展示\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're about to begin a journey that will take us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.79,0:00:33.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从最微小的到无穷大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the infinitesimal to the infinite,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.89,0:00:36.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从时间的开始到遥远的未来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the dawn of time to the distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:41.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们会探索不同的世界和星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'll explore galaxies and suns and worlds,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.23,0:00:44.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在时间和空间的组合中畅游\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}surf the gravity waves of space-time,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.27,0:00:47.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}接触生活在火中和冰中的生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}encounter beings that live in fire and ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.64,0:00:51.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}探索永恒不灭的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}explore the planets of stars that never die,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.41,0:00:53.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}了解和恒星一样大的原子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}discover atoms as massive as suns
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.01,0:00:58.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有比原子还小的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and universes smaller than atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.11,0:01:01.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这也是关于人类的故事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cosmos is also a story about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:10.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这也是先人们对星空研究的史诗长篇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the saga of how wandering bands of hunters and gatherers found their way to the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.16,0:01:13.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}众多英雄共同谱写的史诗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one adventure with many heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.64,0:01:26.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们需要想象力来完成这次历险\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To make this journey,we'll need imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:28.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但仅靠想象力是不够的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But imagination alone is not enough
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.48,0:01:34.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为大自然的真实样子是超乎想象的神奇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the reality of nature is far more wondrous than anything we can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.05,0:01:41.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使这次的历险因为几代研究人员的努力成为可能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This adventure is made possible by generations of searchers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.72,0:01:45.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们严格地坚持一套简单的规则\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}strictly adhering to a simple set of rules...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.23,0:01:49.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以试验和观察结果检验观点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}test ideas by experiment and observation,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.06,0:01:51.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以通过检验的观点为基础\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}build on those ideas that pass the test,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:54.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}摒弃未通过检验的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reject the ones that fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.24,0:01:56.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用证据说话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}follow the evidence wherever it leads
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.87,0:01:59.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并对一切存疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and question everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.54,0:02:02.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}接受这些规则\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Accept these terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.04,0:02:05.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是你的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the cosmos is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.01,0:02:09.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}跟我来吧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.68,0:03:47.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\fe134\fsp0\fad(500,500)\pos(190,278)\fn方正准圆简体\bord0\fs20\c&H24efff&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17\c&Hffffff&} 第一集
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.68,0:03:52.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.82,0:04:02.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这艘想象之舟中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this ship of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:08.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不受空间和时间的限制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}free from the shackles of space and time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.94,0:04:11.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以去任何地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.01,0:04:14.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你想知道我们身处太空何处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you want to see where we are in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.28,0:04:17.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要看向窗外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just look out the front window.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:25.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以时间来说 过去就在我们脚下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the dimension of time, the past lies beneath us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.32,0:04:31.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是地球2.5亿年前的样子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's what Earth looked like 250 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.13,0:04:37.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}抬头 就可以看到未来的样子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you want to see the future, look up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.73,0:04:43.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是2.5亿年后可能的样子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this is how it could appear 250 million years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.37,0:04:45.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们要尝试\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we're going to be venturing out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:48.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在极度广阔的宇宙中联系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the farthest reaches of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.71,0:04:51.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们需要知道自己的宇宙地址\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we need to know our cosmic address,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.65,0:04:55.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是我们地址的第一行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this is the first line of that address.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:04:59.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.06,0:05:21.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们现在离开地球 这个我们仅有的家园\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're leaving the Earth, the only home we've ever known,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.46,0:05:25.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向更加宽广的宇宙进发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the farthest reaches of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.24,0:05:33.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们最近的邻居 月球 没有大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our nearest neighbor, the Moon, has no sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.15,0:05:36.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有海洋 没有生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no ocean, no life...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.58,0:05:39.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有天体撞击的伤痕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just the scars of cosmic impacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:55.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的地球为我们提供了风和浪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our star powers the wind and the waves
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.97,0:05:59.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为地球表面一切的生物提供能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and all the life on the surface of our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.81,0:06:02.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从水星开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun holds all the worlds of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.41,0:06:06.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}整个太阳系都被太阳的引力场所包围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in its gravitational embrace, starting with Mercury...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.50,0:06:29.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到云层覆盖的金星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...to cloud-covered Venus, where runaway greenhouse effect
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:33.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}失控的温室效应把它变成一座炼狱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has turned it into a kind of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.98,0:06:40.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}火星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mars...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.82,0:06:45.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}表面积和地球相近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a world with as much land as Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.00,0:07:01.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一条岩石似的小行星带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A belt of rocky asteroids circles the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.34,0:07:03.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在火星和木星的轨道间围绕太阳运行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the orbits of Mars and Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.32,0:07:19.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}木星被四个大卫星和几十个小卫星环绕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With its four giant moons and dozens of smaller ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.65,0:07:23.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}木星好像拥有自己的太阳系一般\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is like its own little solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.16,0:07:27.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的质量超过所有其它行星的总和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has more mass than all the other planets combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.21,0:07:41.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}木星的大红斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's Great Red Spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.21,0:07:44.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是一个比地球大3倍的古老风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a hurricane three times the size of our whole planet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.38,0:07:48.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}已经存在了几百年之久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's been raging for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.37,0:08:12.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}土星宛如太阳系中皇冠上的明珠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The crown jewel of our solar system, Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.27,0:08:17.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被无数运行轨道和缓慢翻滚的雪球所环绕\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ringed by freeways of countless orbiting and slowly tumbling snowballs...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.95,0:08:21.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个雪球的体积相当于一个小月亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every snowball, a little moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.28,0:08:56.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天王星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Uranus...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.48,0:08:58.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有海王星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and Neptune,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:09:02.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这颗古人未知的最偏远的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the outermost planets, unknown to the ancients
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.82,0:09:07.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到望远镜发明后才被发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and only discovered after the invention of the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:11.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这最偏远的行星之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Beyond the outermost planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:16.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有成千上万的冰冻世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's a swarm of tens of thousands of frozen worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.59,0:09:36.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}冥王星就是其中一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Pluto is one them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.90,0:09:51.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在我们所有的航天器中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of all our spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.34,0:09:54.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是离家最远的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this is the one that's traveled farthest from home...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:57.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者1号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Voyager 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:57.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}于1977年9月5日发射 截止到2012年6月仍然正常运作\n它是有史以来距离地球最远的人造飞行器
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:10:02.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她承载着我们发向未来的信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She bears a message to a billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:10:02.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}历经36年的旅行 离地球约187亿公里 是第一个离开太阳系的人造飞行器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.58,0:10:05.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}关于我们是谁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}something of who we were,
