Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:07.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的体会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how we felt
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.49,0:10:12.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}55种人类语言中包括了四种中国的语言:粤语 国语 闽南语 吴语\n问候语为：「行星地球的孩子（向你们）问好」
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:09.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及我们创作的音乐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the music we made.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:22.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}浩瀚宇宙海洋中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The deeper waters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:24.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更深层的水流里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of this vast cosmic ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:28.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也存在着数不尽的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and their numberless worlds lie ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.89,0:10:44.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从这里看 太阳好像和其它星星并无两样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From out here, the Sun may look like just another star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:47.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但它的引力场依然影响着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it still exerts its gravitational hold
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.23,0:10:49.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}数万亿的冰冻彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on a trillion frozen comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.63,0:10:52.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有太阳系中那些形成于大约50亿年前的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leftovers from the formation of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.40,0:10:55.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其它所有组成部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}nearly five billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.23,0:10:57.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称之为 奥尔特云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called the Oort Cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.87,0:11:00.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以前从没有人见过 也不可能见过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one has ever seen it before, nor could they,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:02.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为这些天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because each one of these little worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.88,0:11:05.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与它最近的邻居之间的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is as far from its nearest neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.11,0:11:08.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和地球与土星的距离差不多 (12-16亿公里）\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as Earth is from Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.75,0:11:12.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个包含太阳系的巨大彗星云团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This enormous cloud of comets encloses the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:16.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是我们宇宙地址的第二行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is the second line of our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.39,0:11:20.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球\n太阳系
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.29,0:11:24.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们有能力探测其它星系的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've only been able to detect the planets of other stars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:26.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是最近几十年的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a few decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.97,0:11:30.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我们已经知道行星的数量是很多的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we already know that planets are plentiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.74,0:11:33.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比恒星的数量要多得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they outnumber the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.41,0:11:36.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎所有的行星都和地球很不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Almost all of them will be very different from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.84,0:11:39.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不适合生物生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and hostile to life as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:41.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我们对于生物又有多少了解呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what do we know about life?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.75,0:11:44.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}目前我们只接触过一种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've met only one kind so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.82,0:11:46.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earthlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:48.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到什么了吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.12,0:11:50.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是空荡荡的太空 对吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just empty space, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:54.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类的眼睛只能看到宇宙中的一丝光亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Human eyes see only a sliver of the light that shines in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.93,0:11:59.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是科技让我们可以看到肉眼无法看到的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But science gives us the power to see what our senses cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.16,0:12:03.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夜视镜可以让我们看见红外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Infrared is the kind of light made visible by night-vision goggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.97,0:12:06.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向黑暗中发射一个红外感应器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Throw an infrared sensor across the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.04,0:12:09.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}流浪行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rogue planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:11.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不绕恒星公转的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}World without a sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.85,0:12:18.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的银河中有数十亿颗游荡在永恒的黑夜中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our galaxy has billions of them, adrift in perpetual night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.32,0:12:21.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他们原本的星系诞生时的混乱中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're orphans, cast away from their mother stars
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.89,0:12:25.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们像孤儿一样失去了恒星母亲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}during the chaotic birth of their native star systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:29.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}流浪行星有着熔岩般的内核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rogue planets are molten at the core
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.73,0:12:31.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但表面却被严寒覆盖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but frozen at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.73,0:12:33.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这些极端区域的中间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There may be oceans of liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.73,0:12:36.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许存在着大洋般的液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the zone between those extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.31,0:12:44.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}谁又能知道水中生活着什么东西呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Who knows what might be swimming there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.68,0:12:52.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是银河的红外线显示图\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what the Milky Way looks like in infrared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.89,0:12:55.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个小点 不仅仅是那些明亮的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every single dot, not just the bright ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.99,0:12:58.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是一颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.19,0:13:00.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这里有多少颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How many stars?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.19,0:13:02.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有多少不同的世界呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How many worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.19,0:13:04.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又有多少不同的生命存在的方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How many ways of being alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:07.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们又身处图片中的何处呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where are we in this picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:10.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到那条螺旋臂了吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See that trailing outer arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:19.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太阳系\n银河系
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.17,0:13:12.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们就在那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's where we live...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.37,0:13:15.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}距离中心3万光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 30,000 light-years from the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.61,0:13:17.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Milky Way Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.34,0:13:20.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们宇宙地址的下一行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the next line of our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.68,0:13:23.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们现在离家十万光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're now a hundred thousand light-years from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:26.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光波 存在的速度最快的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would take light, the fastest thing there is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.35,0:13:30.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要花10万年才能从地球到达我们这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a hundred thousand years to reach us from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.96,0:13:35.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是僊女座螺旋星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the Great Spiral in Andromeda,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.39,0:13:37.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河系的隔壁邻居\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the galaxy next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.40,0:13:39.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们将这两大星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call our two giant galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和一些较小的星系称为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a smattering of smaller ones
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:43.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}本星系群\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the "local group."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.83,0:13:56.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太阳系\n银河系\n本星系群
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.12,0:13:59.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太阳系\n银河系\n本星系群\n室女座超星系团
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:54.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从这里已经看不到银河系了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can't even find our home galaxy from out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.75,0:13:58.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它只是室女座超星系团中的几千份之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's just one of thousands in the Virgo Supercluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.98,0:14:00.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以这个比例来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On this scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.92,0:14:04.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们所看到的 哪怕是最小的点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the objects we see, including the tiniest dots,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.56,0:14:06.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是一个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.39,0:14:08.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个星系包含几十亿颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each galaxy contains billions of suns
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.96,0:14:11.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和数不清的行星世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and countless worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.06,0:14:14.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然而 整个室女座超星系团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yet, the entire Virgo Supercluster itself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.73,0:14:17.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是我们宇宙的一个极小组成部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forms but a tiny part of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.64,0:14:23.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是我们已知的最大范围的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the cosmos on the grandest scale we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.64,0:14:26.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一张由数以千亿的星系组成的大网\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a network of a hundred billion galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:30.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也是我们宇宙地址的最后一行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the last line of our cosmic address...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:32.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}截止目前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:32.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太阳系\n银河系\n本星系群 室女座超星系团\n可观测宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.02,0:14:35.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可观测宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Observable universe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.52,0:14:37.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}什么意思\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.42,0:14:40.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使我们在想象之舟中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even for us, in our Ship of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:43.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在时空中所能看到的也是有限的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's a limit to how far we can see in space-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.83,0:14:46.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是我们的宇宙水平线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's our cosmic horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.27,0:14:49.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一部分的宇宙处于水平线之下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Beyond that horizon lie parts of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.37,0:14:51.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}离我们实在太遥远了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.54,0:14:53.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在仅有的时间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There hasn't been enough time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.54,0:14:56.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在宇宙138亿年的历史中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the 13.8 billion year history of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.64,0:14:59.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光线还来不及传递过来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for their light to have reached us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.18,0:15:04.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很多人猜测 所有的这一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of us suspect that all of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:08.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有的行星 恒星 星系 星团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the worlds, stars, galaxies and clusters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.85,0:15:11.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的可观测宇宙中的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our observable universe...
