Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.26,0:20:10.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他感到一阵不舒服的害怕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He experienced a sickening moment of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.83,0:20:12.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像脚下的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as if the bottom of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.36,0:20:14.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}正向下坠落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was falling away beneath his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.00,0:20:17.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是他鼓起了勇气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But he summoned up his courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:28.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我展开自信的翅膀飞向太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I spread confident wings to space
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.35,0:20:31.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向上高飞至无尽的天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and soared toward the infinite, leaving far behind me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.95,0:20:35.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将一切的压力抛在身后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what others strained to see from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.32,0:20:38.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这里没有上 没有下 没有边界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here, there was no up, no down, no edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.72,0:20:40.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.29,0:20:43.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我看见太阳和其它星星一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I saw that the Sun was just another star,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:47.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有其它被行星伴随着的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the stars were other Suns, each escorted by other Earths
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.70,0:20:49.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.33,0:20:54.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这巨大的启示对他就如同坠入爱河\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The revelation of this immensity was like falling in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.54,0:20:59.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布鲁诺变成了一个传教士\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bruno became an evangelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.54,0:21:02.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他在欧洲各地宣扬他的宇宙无限论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spreading the gospel of infinity throughout Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.98,0:21:06.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他以为其它上帝的追随者会同样接受\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He assumed that other lovers of God would naturally embrace
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.58,0:21:09.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个对于创世的伟大且荣耀的观点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this grander and more glorious view of Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.65,0:21:12.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我是不是太傻了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What a fool I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.73,0:21:18.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他的祖国 他被罗马天主教会开除教籍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He was excommunicated by the Roman Catholic Church in his homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.36,0:21:20.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他不仅被瑞士加尔文长老会驱逐出境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}expelled by the Calvinists in Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.83,0:21:23.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还被德国的路德教派驱逐出境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and by the Lutherans in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.07,0:21:28.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布鲁诺接受了一份邀请到英国牛津大学讲课\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bruno jumped at an invitation to lecture at Oxford, in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.34,0:21:32.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他认为这是一个机会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At last, he thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.21,0:21:35.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以与他类似的人分享他的观点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a chance to share his vision with an audience of his peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.95,0:21:43.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我来介绍一个对于宇宙的崭新看法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I have come to present a new vision of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.05,0:21:46.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哥白尼是对的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Copernicus was right to argue that our world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.12,0:21:47.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的世界并不是宇宙的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is not the center of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.86,0:21:49.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球绕着太阳旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth goes around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.93,0:21:52.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它和其它行星一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a planet, just like the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.43,0:21:54.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但哥白尼只是曙光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Copernicus was only the dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.53,0:21:56.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而我为你们带来日出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I bring you the sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.10,0:22:00.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些星星和我们炙热的太阳一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars are other fiery suns,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.20,0:22:02.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由和地球一样的天体组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}made of the same substance as the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:05.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们也有自己的含水的地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they have their own watery earths,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.48,0:22:08.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上面有着和我们一样高贵的动物植物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with plants and animals no less noble than our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.58,0:22:10.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你是疯了还是太蠢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are you mad or merely ignorant?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.88,0:22:12.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}众所周知只有一个世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everyone knows there is only one world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.65,0:22:15.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是错误的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What everyone knows is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.15,0:22:18.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们全能的上帝创造了一个无边无际的宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our infinite God has created a boundless universe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.16,0:22:20.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其中包含了无数的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with an infinite number of worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:22.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你们那的人没读过亚里士多德的书吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Do they not read Aristotle where you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.09,0:22:23.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者是圣经吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or even the Bible?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.83,0:22:28.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我请求你摒弃老旧和传统的信仰和权威\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I beg you, reject antiquity, tradition, faith, and authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.47,0:22:29.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我们重新认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let us begin anew,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.77,0:22:31.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}质疑我们以为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by doubting everything we assume
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.80,0:22:32.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}-已经被证实的一切 -异端者!\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}- has been proven. - Heretic!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.94,0:22:33.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}异教徒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Infidel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.01,0:22:35.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你们信仰的上帝太小了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Your God is too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.45,0:22:43.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}明智的人本应该从中吸取了教训\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A wiser man would have learned his lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.85,0:22:47.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可惜布鲁诺并不是那个人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Bruno was not such a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.19,0:22:51.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他不停的宣扬自己观点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He couldn't keep his soaring vision of the cosmos to himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.46,0:22:54.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽管这会带来沉痛的代价\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}despite the fact that the penalty for doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.43,0:22:57.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他的那个时代 代价是如此的残酷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in his world was the most vicious form
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.46,0:22:59.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无情和更严厉的惩罚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of cruel and unusual punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.07,0:23:07.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}焦尔达诺·布鲁诺生活的那个时代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Giordano Bruno lived at a time when there was no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.77,0:23:09.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有政教分离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the separation of church and state,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.74,0:23:14.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有言论自由神圣不可侵犯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or the notion that freedom of speech was a sacred right of every individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.28,0:23:17.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}表达与传统信仰相悖的观点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Expressing an idea that didn't conform to traditional belief
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.15,0:23:19.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会带来极大的麻烦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could land you in deep trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:24.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布鲁诺不顾一切地回到了意大利\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recklessly, Bruno returned to Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.45,0:23:26.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许是想家了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe he was homesick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.12,0:23:29.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可是他必须知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But still, he must have known that his homeland
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.39,0:23:31.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的祖国对他来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was one of the most dangerous places in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.49,0:23:33.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是最危险的国家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he could possibly go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:36.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由罗马天主教会管辖的宗教法庭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Roman Catholic Church maintained a system of courts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.33,0:23:38.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被称为异端裁判所\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known as the Inquisition,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.17,0:23:41.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它唯一职责就是审查和折磨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its sole purpose was to investigate and torment
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.74,0:23:45.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与教会持有不同声音和观点的人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}anyone who dared voice views that differed from theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.65,0:23:52.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布鲁诺很快就被\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It wasn't long before Bruno fell into the clutches
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.62,0:23:54.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}思想警察抓获\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the thought police.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.52,0:24:03.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这位信奉无限宇宙的流浪者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This wanderer, who worshiped an infinite universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.19,0:24:06.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在八年的监狱生涯中饱受煎熬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}languished in confinement for eight years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.36,0:24:08.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽管受尽残酷的审讯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Through relentless interrogations,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.20,0:24:10.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他依然不愿放弃他的观点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he stubbornly refused to renounce his views.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.93,0:24:12.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么教会要花\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why was the Church willing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.50,0:24:16.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如此长的时间来折磨布鲁诺\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to go to such lengths to torment Bruno?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.21,0:24:18.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们在害怕什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What were they afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.62,0:24:21.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果布鲁诺是对的 那么这些圣典\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If Bruno was right, then the sacred books
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.86,0:24:24.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有教会的权威\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the authority of the Church
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.71,0:24:28.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都将会受到质疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would be open to question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.92,0:24:28.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最终 异端裁判所的红衣主教们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finally, the cardinals of the Inquisition
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.66,0:24:30.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}做出了他们的判决\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rendered their verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.59,0:24:32.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你有罪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You are found guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.19,0:24:35.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你质疑圣父圣子圣灵三位一体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of questioning the Holy Trinity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.06,0:24:37.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你质疑耶稣基督的神威\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.76,0:24:41.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你相信上帝的怒火不会永远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of believing that God's wrath is not eternal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.07,0:24:42.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有人都会被宽恕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that everyone will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.57,0:24:47.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你断言其它世界存在的主张\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of asserting the existence of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.51,0:24:51.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你写的所有书\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of the books you have written
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.44,0:24:54.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都会在圣彼得广场前焚毁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will be gathered up and burned in St. Peter's Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.95,0:24:58.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尊敬的大人 8年的监禁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Reverend Father, these eight years of confinement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.55,0:25:00.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给了我很多时间去反省\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have given me much time to reflect.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.12,0:25:01.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.12,0:25:02.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你要放弃你的主张吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you will recant?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.52,0:25:04.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我对造物主的爱和崇敬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My love and reverence for the Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.52,0:25:08.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}激发我对全能的上帝的认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inspires in me the vision of an infinite Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.20,0:25:11.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你拒不忏悔的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You shall be turned over to the Governor of Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.80,0:25:15.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你会被移交到罗马总督\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to administer the appropriate punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.20,0:25:17.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}予以执行相应的惩罚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for those who will not repent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.37,0:25:23.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可能你宣布这个判决时的恐惧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It may be that you are more afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.31,0:25:26.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比我听到判决的时候更厉害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to deliver this judgment than I am to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.78,0:26:37.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布鲁诺殉难的10年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ten years after Bruno's martyrdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.05,0:26:39.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}伽利略通过望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galileo first looked through a telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.52,0:26:42.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现布鲁诺的学说确实没错\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}realizing that Bruno had been right all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.19,0:26:46.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河系是由肉眼看不到的无数恒星组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Milky Way was made of countless stars invisible to the naked eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.69,0:26:50.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天空中的某些光亮其实是其它的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and some of those lights in the sky were actually other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.66,0:26:52.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布鲁诺不是科学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bruno was no scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.97,0:26:55.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他只是侥幸猜中了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His vision of the cosmos was a lucky guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.47,0:26:57.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为没有证据支持他\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because he had no evidence to support it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.97,0:27:01.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就和其它猜想一样 也有可能不对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like most guesses, it could well have turned out wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.24,0:27:03.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是这个观点一旦散播出去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But once the idea was in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.84,0:27:05.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就给了其它人一个方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it gave others a target to aim at.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.91,0:27:07.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哪怕只是为了反驳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If only to disprove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.55,0:27:13.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布鲁诺大致理解了太空的浩瀚无垠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bruno glimpsed the vastness of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.25,0:27:18.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但他对于时间的惊人无际没有丝毫概念\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But he had no inkling of the staggering immensity of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.60,0:27:24.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}寿命很少超过一个世纪的普通人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How can we humans, who rarely live more than a century,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.70,0:27:27.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}怎么可能去理解宇宙的历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hope to grasp the vast expanse of time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.50,0:27:29.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像浩瀚宽阔的时间长河\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is the history of the cosmos?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.74,0:27:34.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙诞生于138亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe is 13.8 thousand million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.54,0:27:36.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了更好地想象宇宙的历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In order to imagine all of cosmic time,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.94,0:27:40.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们把它压缩成12个月的年历\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}let's compress it into a single calendar year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.71,0:27:58.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}年历上的1月1号是宇宙诞生的日子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cosmic calendar begins on January 1st with the birth of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.73,0:28:01.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}年历上包含了从那以后经历的所有时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It contains everything that's happened since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.42,0:28:02.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一直到现在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}up to now,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.80,0:28:07.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这个年历上的12月31号午夜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which on this calendar is midnight December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.35,0:28:11.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}按照这个比例 每个月代表10亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On this scale, every month represents about a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.32,0:28:15.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每天代表将就4千万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every day represents nearly 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.88,0:28:17.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我们尽可能地回到过去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's go back as far as we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.77,0:28:20.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}回到宇宙最开始的时刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the very first moment of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.86,0:28:25.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1月1号 宇宙大爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}January 1st, the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.59,0:28:42.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}目前而言这是我们所能看到最早的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's as far back as we can see in time... for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.22,0:28:47.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}整个宇宙形成于一个比原子还小的点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our entire universe emerged from a point smaller than a single atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.05,0:28:51.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}空间在密度极大温度极高的状态下爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space itself exploded in a cosmic fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.05,0:28:53.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由此开始了宇宙的扩张\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}launching the expansion of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.42,0:28:55.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并诞生了所有的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and giving birth to all the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.82,0:28:57.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有已经产生的那些所有我们已知的事物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and all the matter we know today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.79,0:29:00.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}听上去很疯狂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I know that sounds crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.12,0:29:02.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我们有很强力的观测证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but there's strong observational evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.09,0:29:03.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来支持宇宙大爆炸理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to support the Big Bang theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.73,0:29:06.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}证据还有氦元素在宇宙中的比例\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it includes the amount of helium in the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.23,0:29:09.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及爆炸残留的发光无线电频谱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the glow of radio waves left over from the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.90,0:29:12.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爆炸后宇宙开始冷却\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it expanded, the universe cooled,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.40,0:29:17.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其间有2亿年左右的黑暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there was darkness for about 200 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.31,0:29:20.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}万有引力将气体集聚并且加热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity was pulling together clumps of gas and heating them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.80,0:29:23.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到第一批恒星发出亮光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until the first stars burst into light
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.80,0:29:26.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相当于1月10号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on January 10th.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.94,0:29:34.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1月13号 这些恒星开始结合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On January 13th, these stars coalesced
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.78,0:29:39.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}形成第一批小星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the first small galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.68,0:29:42.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些星系融合成更大的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These galaxies merged to form still larger ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.52,0:29:45.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括我们的银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including our own Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.89,0:29:50.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}产生于110亿年左右\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which formed about 11 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.36,0:29:53.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是宇宙年历上的3月15号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on March 15th of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.07,0:29:57.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}数千亿的恒星中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hundreds of billions of suns.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.57,0:29:59.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哪个是我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which one is ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.40,0:30:01.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此时尚未诞生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not yet born.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.64,0:30:06.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它将从其它恒星的灰烬中产生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will rise from the ashes of other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.14,0:30:09.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到这些犹如闪光灯般的亮光吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See those lights flashing like paparazzi?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.38,0:30:11.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们都是超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each one is a supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.85,0:30:14.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一颗超大恒星的耀眼爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the blazing death of a giant star.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.02,0:30:18.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星消亡和诞生的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars die and are born in places like this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.42,0:30:20.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称为星星苗圃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a stellar nursery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.42,0:30:20.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}又称分子云
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.32,0:30:21.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们像雨滴般\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They condense like raindrops
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.03,0:30:24.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从巨大的气态和灰尘云中凝结\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from giant clouds of gas and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.70,0:30:27.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们温度高的可以把原子中的原子核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They get so hot that the nuclei of the atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.70,0:30:30.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}融合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fuse together deep within them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.23,0:30:33.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从而产生了我们呼吸的氧气 肌肉中的碳元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to make the oxygen we breathe, the carbon in our muscles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.44,0:30:36.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}骨头中的钙元素 血中的铁元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the calcium in our bones, the iron in our blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.91,0:30:38.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有的这一切都产生于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all of it was cooked
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.71,0:30:42.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从此消亡的恒星炙热的内心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the fiery hearts of long-vanished stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.21,0:30:45.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你 我 所有人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You, me, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.95,0:30:50.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们都是由星辰物质组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we are made of star stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.19,0:30:54.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星辰物质被不断循环和浓缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This star stuff is recycled and enriched,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.52,0:30:56.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一遍又一遍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}again and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.09,0:30:58.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}经过几代恒星的诞生消亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through succeeding generations of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.03,0:31:05.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}离我们的太阳诞生还有多久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How much longer until the birth of our Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.44,0:31:07.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很长时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.24,0:31:08.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们太阳的第一次发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It won't begin to shine
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.54,0:31:11.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还要再等60亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for another six billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.08,0:31:16.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳的生日是8月31号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun's birthday is August 31st
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.08,0:31:17.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这个宇宙年历上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the Cosmic Calendar...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.42,0:31:22.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}45亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...four and a half billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.72,0:31:25.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像太阳系中其它行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As with the other worlds of our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.22,0:31:28.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球在一堆气体和灰尘中产生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth was formed from a disk of gas and dust
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.33,0:31:30.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}绕着新生的太阳运行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orbiting the newborn Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.49,0:31:33.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}反复的碰撞产生了一个发光的球状碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Repeated collisions produced a growing ball of debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.34,0:31:41.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到那个小行星了吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See that asteroid?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.77,0:31:43.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不是那个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No, not that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.11,0:31:44.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那边的那个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The one over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.81,0:31:48.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的存在归功于它旁边的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We exist because the gravity of that one next to it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.58,0:31:51.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把它轻轻向左推了一英吋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just nudged it an inch to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.75,0:31:53.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一英吋有很大的区别吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What difference could an inch make
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.78,0:31:55.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}按照太阳系的比例来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the scale the solar system?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.85,0:31:58.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}稍等 你马上就能看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just wait, you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.32,0:32:02.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在最初的10亿年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth took one hell of a beating
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.16,0:32:03.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球饱受摧残\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in its first billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.43,0:32:10.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}任由轨道上的碎片撞击和融合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fragments of orbiting debris collided and coalesced,
